      "message": "Validation on eth0/channel 0x01 shows the patch works before restart: setting IPFamilyEnables to IPv4Only succeeds, Get LAN returns 11 00, and IPv6AcceptRA/DHCP6 become false. However, after restarting phosphor-ipmi-host.service, Get LAN returns 11 02 (DualStack) while IPv6AcceptRA/DHCP6 remain false on the interface. This indicates a post-restart reporting mismatch (volatile state reset) and Get LAN is not reflecting effective runtime configuration after service restart.\n\nTesting Result:\n\nRemote:\n\nmegarac@megarac-desktop:~$ ipmitool -H 172.16.97.11 -U root -P 0penBmc -I lanplus -C 17 raw 0x0c 0x01 0x01 0x33 0x00\n\nmegarac@megarac-desktop:$ ipmitool -H 172.16.97.11 -U root -P 0penBmc -I lanplus -C 17 raw 0x0c 0x02 0x01 0x33 0x00 0x00\n11 00\nmegarac@megarac-desktop:$\n\n\nBMC:\n\nroot@evb-ast2600:# busctl get-property xyz.openbmc_project.Network /xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth0 xyz.openbmc_project.Network.EthernetInterface IPv6AcceptRA\nb false\nroot@evb-ast2600:# busctl get-property xyz.openbmc_project.Network /xyz/openbmc_project/network/eth0 xyz.openbmc_project.Network.EthernetInterface DHCP6\nb false\nroot@evb-ast2600:#\nroot@evb-ast2600:#\nroot@evb-ast2600:# systemctl restart phosphor-ipmi-host.service\nroot@evb-ast2600:# systemctl status phosphor-ipmi-host.service\n\nphosphor-ipmi-host.service - Phosphor Inband IPMI\nLoaded: loaded (8;;file://evb-ast2600/usr/lib/systemd/system/phosphor-ipmi-host.service/usr/lib/systemd/system/phosphor-ipmi-host.service8;;; enabled; preset: enabled)\nDrop-In: /usr/lib/systemd/system/phosphor-ipmi-host.service.d\n-8;;file://evb-ast2600/usr/lib/systemd/system/phosphor-ipmi-host.service.d/10-override.conf10-override.conf8;;    Active: active (running) since Wed 2026-07-01 08:50:39 UTC; 12s ago  Invocation: c9b72d3c729a433c858655ec6ddd8b45  Main PID: 540 (ipmid)   CPU: 184ms    CGroup: /system.slice/phosphor-ipmi-host.service        -5:245m540 ipmid\nJul 01 08:50:38 evb-ast2600 systemd[1]: Starting Phospho